   <body>
      <ol>
         <li>
            <p>Before starting the work instruction activity, perform the following steps:</p>
            <ol id="substeps_qv3_zdy_wcc">
               <li>
                  <p>Do not begin these tasks without confirmation that personnel directly
                     involved have completed the required training associated with the work
                     instruction activity and have reviewed this document.</p>
               </li>
               <li>
                  <p>Gather necessary tools and equipment as identified below in the Equipment
                     Section.</p>
               </li>
               <li>
                  <p>Wear and use additional Personal Protective Equipment (PPE) and safety
                     equipment required for this specific work instruction.</p>
               </li>
               <li>
                  <p>Obey all applicable safety requirements and procedures.</p>
               </li>
               <li>
                  <p>Notify appropriate personnel of the activity and estimated time needed to
                     complete the tasks.</p>
               </li>
               <li>
                  <p>Follow all Lockout Tagout procedures when work instruction activity requires
                     isolating energy in the designated area. Verify energy is isolated before
                     starting work.</p>
               </li>
            </ol>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>For container handling setup, perform the following steps:</p>
            <ol id="substeps_mdq_fhy_wcc">
               <li>
                  <p>The HMI screen of the Multi 4 is located on the front right door of the
                     machine.</p>
                  <p>
                     <p>
                        <fig id="fig_zcr_hhy_wcc">
                           <image href="media/image1.jpg"
                                  placement="break"
                                  id="image_jjb_mjy_wcc"
                                  align="center"/>
                        </fig>
                     </p>
                  </p>
               </li>
               <li>
                  <p>From the main screen, Click on the <uicontrol>LOG</uicontrol> button and
                     login to the software using the password.</p>
                  <p>
                     <p>
                        <fig id="fig_hz1_jhy_wcc">
                           <image href="media/image2.jpg"
                                  placement="break"
                                  id="image_l5l_njy_wcc"
                                  align="center"/>
                        </fig>
                     </p>
                  </p>
               </li>
               <li>
                  <p>Open the Article Menu– this contains a list of all job history.</p>
                  <p>
                     <p>
                        <fig id="fig_nfm_khy_wcc">
                           <image href="media/image3.jpg"
                                  placement="break"
                                  id="image_qhm_4jy_wcc"
                                  align="center"/>
                        </fig>
                     </p>
                  </p>
               </li>
               <li>
                  <p>Load job history if available. If not available, use default settings or use
                     a similar setup article.</p>
                  <p>
                     <ol id="ol_jqx_lhy_wcc">
                        <li>Click on an <uicontrol>existing article</uicontrol> (with a shape as
                           similar as possible as the new one).</li>
                        <li>Click on “<uicontrol>copy article</uicontrol>”.</li>
                        <li> Write and enter the name of the new article (16 characters
                           Maximum).</li>
                        <li>Select the new article and click on “<uicontrol>Load</uicontrol>”: The
                           article is loaded in the electronic board.</li>
                        <li>Existing article</li>
                     </ol>
                     <p>
                        <fig id="fig_sgg_tjy_wcc">
                           <image href="media/image4.jpg"
                                  placement="break"
                                  id="image_h45_tjy_wcc"
                                  align="center"/>
                        </fig>
                     </p>
                  </p>
               </li>
               <li>
                  <p>Select the article and click on “<uicontrol>Load</uicontrol>”.</p>
                  <p>
                     <p>
                        <fig id="fig_fjn_thy_wcc">
                           <image href="media/image5.jpg"
                                  placement="break"
                                  id="image_afr_5jy_wcc"
                                  align="center"/>
                        </fig>
                     </p>
                  </p>
               </li>
               <li>
                  <p>Exit the Article menu </p>
               </li>
               <li>
                  <p> Stop the flow of containers into the machine.</p>
                  <p>
                     <p>
                        <fig id="fig_b3g_why_wcc">
                           <image href="media/image6.jpg"
                                  placement="break"
                                  id="image_f52_wjy_wcc"
                                  align="center"/>
                        </fig>
                     </p>
                  </p>
               </li>
               <li>
                  <p>Using the key operated switch, place the machine into manual mode.</p>
                  <p>
                     <p>
                        <fig id="fig_hyr_xhy_wcc">
                           <image href="media/image7.jpg"
                                  placement="break"
                                  id="image_mhr_xjy_wcc"
                                  align="center"/>
                        </fig>
                     </p>
                  </p>
               </li>
               <li>
                  <p>Adjust the panel at the infeed based on the size of the container to reduce
                     the amount of stray light that will enter the container.</p>
                  <p>
                     <ol id="ol_s4h_b3y_wcc">
                        <li>If needed, remove the infeed and outfeed panels so that large containers
                           can run through the machine.</li>
                     </ol>
                     <p>
                        <fig id="fig_ibk_c3y_wcc">
                           <image href="media/image8.jpg"
                                  placement="break"
                                  id="image_xjx_yjy_wcc"
                                  align="center"/>
                        </fig>
                     </p>
                  </p>
               </li>
               <li>
                  <p> Confirm proper spacing of the containers using the spacing device prior to
                     Multistation or MCAL.</p>
                  <p>
                     <ol id="ol_lc2_23y_wcc">
                        <li>A minimum of 1.5 container diameters is required for the Multi, but
                           spacing can be more if paired with another machine using the same
                           spacer.</li>
                     </ol>
                     <p>
                        <fig id="fig_hfm_f3y_wcc">
                           <image href="media/image9.jpg"
                                  placement="break"
                                  id="image_wbp_1ky_wcc"
                                  align="center"/>
                           <image href="media/image10.jpg"
                                  placement="break"
                                  id="image_ek5_bky_wcc"
                                  align="center"/>
                        </fig>
                     </p>
                  </p>
               </li>
               <li>
                  <p>Look through the spacing device to visually confirm the container’s stability
                     on the conveyor at maximum production speed. If stability is an issue, adjust
                     the following:</p>
                  <p>
                     <ol id="ol_hc1_h3y_wcc">
                        <li>Conveyor if not level</li>
                        <li>Spacer (especially the condition of the belts) for proper position on
                           the conveyor.</li>
                     </ol>
                  </p>
               </li>
               <li>
                  <p>Open the cabinet door on the front of the machine.</p>
               </li>
               <li>
                  <p>Remove or add belts depending on the container height.</p>
                  <p>
                     <ol id="ol_l45_n3y_wcc">
                        <li> Verify the condition of the belts and replace if needed.</li>
                        <li>Using a container that is specific to the job being run, adjust the
                           height of the belts to achieve the best grip on the container.</li>
                     </ol>
                     <p>
                        <fig id="fig_ink_p3y_wcc">
                           <image href="media/image11.jpg"
                                  placement="break"
                                  id="image_p5n_2ky_wcc"
                                  align="center"/>
                        </fig>
                     </p>
                  </p>
               </li>
               <li>
                  <p>Jog a setup container (specific to the job change being performed) into the
                     entry of the machine.</p>
                  <p>
                     <ol id="ol_q3n_r3y_wcc">
                        <li>Jog the container using the manual jog switch.</li>
                        <li>Manual switch allows container movement in both directions.</li>
                     </ol>
                  </p>
               </li>
               <li>
                  <p>Check the operation of the infeed photocell and adjust the sensitivity as
                     needed.</p>
                  <p>
                     <p>
                        <fig id="fig_vms_t3y_wcc">
                           <image href="media/image12.jpg"
                                  placement="break"
                                  id="image_q2j_hjy_wcc"
                                  align="center"/>
                        </fig>
                     </p>
                  </p>
               </li>
               <li>
                  <p>Using a container that is specific to the job being run, adjust the spacing
                     between the belts at the entry of the machine.</p>
                  <p>
                     <ol id="ol_iqd_x3y_wcc">
                        <li>Adapt belt spacing to the diameter of the container using the
                           crank.</li>
                        <li>Recommended foam compression is 2-3 mm against the container.</li>
                     </ol>
                     <p>
                        <fig id="fig_tqy_y3y_wcc">
                           <image href="media/image13.jpg"
                                  placement="break"
                                  id="image_txf_lky_wcc"
                                  align="center"/>
                           <image href="media/image14.jpg"
                                  placement="break"
                                  id="image_svq_mky_wcc"
                                  align="center"/>
                           <image href="media/image15.jpg"
                                  placement="break"
                                  id="image_ghv_nky_wcc"
                                  align="center"/>
                        </fig>
                     </p>
                  </p>
               </li>
               <li>
                  <p>Adjust height of all cameras and light sources as a container is slowly
                     jogged through the machine to avoid interferences. If loading an existing job,
                     set height according to recorded value.</p>
                  <p>
                     <p>
                        <fig id="fig_qbn_1jy_wcc">
                           <image href="media/image16.jpg"
                                  placement="break"
                                  id="image_onq_pky_wcc"
                                  align="center"/>
                        </fig>
                     </p>
                  </p>
               </li>
               <li>
                  <p>This machine can be equipped with several devices and could be installed in a
                     different order.</p>
                  <p>
                     <ol id="ol_mqb_cjy_wcc">
                        <li>MCF</li>
                        <li>Base Stress</li>
                        <li>CSBC</li>
                        <li>CSBC-LO</li>
                        <li>LNMC</li>
                        <li>CRBC (not covered in this document)</li>
                        <li>BNR (not covered in this document)</li>
                        <li> LNMP (not covered in this document) </li>
                     </ol>
                  </p>
               </li>
            </ol>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>For setup of the ejector(s) for all stations, perform the following steps:</p>
            <ol id="substeps_gmx_sky_wcc">
               <li>
                  <p>Put the machine into automatic mode.</p>
                  <p>
                     <p>
                        <fig id="fig_rhp_xky_wcc">
                           <image href="media/image17.jpg"
                                  placement="break"
                                  id="image_rcz_jly_wcc"
                                  align="center"/>
                        </fig>
                     </p>
                  </p>
               </li>
               <li>
                  <p>Open the Distances menu.</p>
                  <p>
                     <p>
                        <fig id="fig_rcd_yky_wcc">
                           <image href="media/image18.jpg"
                                  placement="break"
                                  id="image_klf_lly_wcc"
                                  align="center"/>
                        </fig>
                     </p>
                  </p>
               </li>
               <li>
                  <p>Turn on the test of the ejector 1 and 2 if installed.</p>
                  <p>
                     <p>
                        <fig id="fig_dlt_yky_wcc">
                           <image href="media/image19.jpg"
                                  placement="break"
                                  id="image_th4_ply_wcc"
                                  align="center"/>
                        </fig>
                     </p>
                  </p>
               </li>
               <li>
                  <p>Pass a container through the machine and physically stand in front of the
                     reject.</p>
               </li>
               <li>
                  <p>For ejector 1, adjust the distance between the device and the ejector until
                     the blower is performing optimally.</p>
               </li>
               <li>
                  <p>Repeat for ejector 2 if needed.</p>
               </li>
               <li>
                  <p>For ejector 1 and ejector 2 if installed, set the delay in ms (blowing time)
                     to achieve proper ejection of the container.</p>
                  <p>
                     <ol id="ol_kkb_cly_wcc">
                        <li>Delay time depends on container size and line speed. </li>
                     </ol>
                     <p>
                        <fig id="fig_myv_cly_wcc">
                           <image href="media/image20.jpg"
                                  placement="break"
                                  id="image_uvk_xly_wcc"
                                  align="center"/>
                        </fig>
                     </p>
                  </p>
               </li>
               <li>
                  <p>Switch off test mode and press the green check.</p>
               </li>
               <li>
                  <p>Perform device setup for each device installed and required for the job to be
                     run using the appropriate work instruction (s)</p>
                  <p>
                     <ol id="ol_pxy_2ly_wcc">
                        <li>INS-03-037 CSBC LO</li>
                        <li> INS-03-067 CSBC </li>
                        <li>INS-03-068 LNMC</li>
                        <li>INS-03-061 MCF</li>
                        <li>INS-03-064 Base Stress</li>
                     </ol>
                  </p>
               </li>
            </ol>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Upon completion of tasks, perform the following steps:</p>
            <ol id="substeps_qtp_yly_wcc">
               <li>
                  <p>Confirm the designated work area is clear and communicate to personnel the
                     intent to restart energy.</p>
               </li>
               <li>
                  <p>Perform basic housekeeping duties. Clean up the work space, tools and
                     equipment, dispose of trash, put tools and equipment in assigned area.</p>
               </li>
               <li>
                  <p>Notify appropriate personnel that the work instruction activity has been
                     completed.</p>
               </li>
               <li>
                  <p>Record and report findings and results.</p>
               </li>
               <li>
                  <p>Follow appropriate instructions for notification of findings and results
                     relating to specifications, targets and/or reaction limits.</p>
               </li>
            </ol>
         </li>
      </ol>
   </body>
